item.title: Need 465 updater output :x
item.dc:creator: @frank frank_
item.description:
@frank wrote:

[quote=“Taios, post:4, topic:126757”]Silver was giving you the info so you could find it yourself ;). The info he gave is really, more valuable then the actual field name.

Check this out :

if ((class68_sub10_sub7_sub3.anInt3358 ^ 0xffffffff) < (Class73.anInt1512 ^ 0xffffffff)) { Class68_Sub3.method650(class68_sub10_sub7_sub3, (class68_sub10_sub7_sub3.anInt3393 + 15), -48); if ((Applet_Sub1.anInt27 ^ 0xffffffff) < 0) { int i_6_ = (30 * class68_sub10_sub7_sub3.anInt3381 / class68_sub10_sub7_sub3.anInt3422); if ((i_6_ ^ 0xffffffff) < -31) i_6_ = 30;

Theres lots of other goodies in this method aswell. anInt3358 is loop status or cycle. anInt3381 current health, anInt3422 max health.
Check bipush 30 or 31.[/quote]imo the (sipush aload getfield)|(aload getfield sipush) imul is easier
